File: platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.ts. Add after postForm.

IMPORTANT: Do NOT set Content-Type header — the browser must set it automatically with the multipart boundary string. If you set it manually, the boundary will be missing and the server will reject the request.

Pattern:
```typescript
export const postFormData: {
  <T>(url: string, body: FormData, init?: RequestInit): Promise<T>;
  <T>(url: string, body: FormData, init: RequestInit | undefined, schema: z.ZodType<T>): Promise<T>;
} = async <T>(url: string, body: FormData, init?: RequestInit, schema?: z.ZodType<T>): Promise<T> => {
  const response = await fetchFromPage(url, {
    method: 'POST',
    body,
    ...init,
    headers: { ...init?.headers },  // no Content-Type!
  });
  // ... same JSON parse + optional schema validation as postJSON
};
```

Export from platform/plugin-sdk/src/index.ts alongside the other fetch utilities.
